<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-15T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-15T18:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">580.7A3/413: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-15T18:00:00-05:00">April 15, 1929—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>84. Your telegram No. 84, April 14, 8 p.m. You may accept the first
                            proposal, that is to agree to the adoption of the clause which reads:
                            “Each country shall be entitled to one vote.”</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>